laboratory_examinations.findings: Frequent sampling revealed detectable but apulsatile LH and FSH release.
Spontaneous FSH and LH release was detected throughout the day and night, but there was no autocorrelation and a poorly defined rapid Fourier transform of low spectral power.
Despite gonadotropin responses to LHRH stimulation, testosterone remained persistently low.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Induced puberty with increasing doses of testosterone.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Borderline oligospermia (18 million sperm/ml, 67% abnormal forms, 60% motility).

laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Persistently low testosterone despite gonadotropin responses.
